Kaduna State Government on Friday, condemned the killing, kidnapping and destruction of property in six villages of Giwa Local Government Area of the state. Samuel Aruwan Commissioner, Ministry of Internal Security and Home Affairs, Kaduna State in a statement on Friday, while confirming that dozens have been killed, while several others were abducted by kidnappers who stormed the communities, said the attacks occurred between Thursday and the early hours of today. He said the Kaduna State Government is still awaiting detailed security report He said the affected villages were Dillalai, Barebari, Dokan Alhaji Yaâ€™u, Durumi, Kaya and Fatika. According to him, the Kaduna State Government is still awaiting a full report of the attacks and will make this public as soon as details are received from security forces.